  <section class="section" id="g-scenarios">
    <div class="section-tag">🟦 terragrunt · 04 · ⚠ daily ops</div>
    <h2>Real Office Issues — Terragrunt</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">The specific ways Terragrunt setups go wrong, beyond the regular Terraform issues above.</p>

    <details class="item issue-item">
      <summary><span class="issue-badge">issue</span> "Could not find terragrunt.hcl" or "no terraform files found"<span class="arrow">▾</span></summary>
      <div class="item-body">
        <h4>Why it happens</h4>
        <p>Running a Terragrunt command from the wrong directory, or the <code>source</code> path in <code>terraform { source = ... }</code> points somewhere that doesn't actually contain the module.</p>
        <h4>How to investigate</h4>
        <pre><span class="c"># confirm you're in the right leaf folder (live/&lt;env&gt;/&lt;component&gt;)</span>
pwd
<span class="c"># check the source path actually resolves correctly relative to this file</span>
cat terragrunt.hcl</pre>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="item issue-item">
      <summary><span class="issue-badge">issue</span> <code>dependency</code> block fails because the dependency hasn't been applied yet<span class="arrow">▾</span></summary>
      <div class="item-body">
        <h4>Why it happens</h4>
        <p>You're trying to <code>plan</code>/<code>apply</code> a module that depends on another module's outputs, but that other module has never been successfully applied — there's no real state to read outputs from.</p>
        <h4>How to fix</h4>
        <pre><span class="c"># option 1: apply the dependency first</span>
cd ../vpc &amp;&amp; terragrunt apply

<span class="c"># option 2: add mock_outputs in the terragrunt.hcl so plan works anyway</span>
dependency "vpc" {
  config_path = "../vpc"
  mock_outputs = {
    vpc_id = "vpc-00000000"
  }
}</pre>
        <div class="scenario-box">
          <span class="box-label">real office scenario</span>
          This is the classic "brand new environment" problem — spinning up a fresh staging environment from scratch, where nothing exists yet. <code>mock_outputs</code> lets you still run <code>plan</code> across the whole tree to sanity-check the configuration before the real dependency chain has anything to read from.
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="item issue-item">
      <summary><span class="issue-badge">issue</span> Same change applied differently across environments — drift between dev/staging/prod<span class="arrow">▾</span></summary>
      <div class="item-body">
        <h4>Why it happens</h4>
        <p>Someone edited an environment-specific <code>terragrunt.hcl</code>'s <code>inputs</code> directly instead of updating the shared module or a common variable, so environments silently diverge over time.</p>
        <h4>How to fix</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Push genuinely shared logic (not just values) up into the module itself, or into the root <code>terragrunt.hcl</code>'s shared <code>inputs</code>/<code>locals</code>, rather than letting each environment fork its own copy.</li>
          <li>Periodically run <code>run-all plan</code> across all environments and review — drift in the plan output for environments you didn't intend to touch is a signal something's misaligned.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>
  </section>

